our commitment to team building and partnering. He began his career at Superior Construction as a field engineer in 1995, and his leadership and vision, balanced with a commitment to secure our core family values, has built lasting relationships and increased market share for the company. Dan graduated from Purdue University with a bachelor\u2019s degree in civil engineering. He is actively involved in multiple organizations and is currently serving as president for the Construction Advancement Foundation.<\/span> <\/p>\n<h3>Kevin McGlinchey<\/h3>\n<h4>President, Southeast Business Unit<\/h4>\n<p>Kevin brings three decades of heavy civil construction experience to his role as president of the Southeast Business Unit. He has helped lead numerous award-winning projects in his career, including dozens of transportation-related contracts totaling more than $5 billion in Florida alone. Kevin oversees Superior&#8217;s operations and business development for projects across the Southeast, from Tennessee to Florida to the Carolinas. He earned a bachelor&#8217;s degree in civil engineering from California Polytechnic State University \u2013 San Luis Obispo and maintains a certified general contractor license in Florida.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Nick Largura Chief Executive Officer As the fourth-generation owner and operator, Nick\u2019s vision and commitment are at the core of our continued growth and success. Nick grew up with a deep interest in construction and the business and spent every opportunity available working within the company and alongside those who built it. He fostered his [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":8,"menu_order":2,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"inline_featured_image":false,"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"footnotes":""}